{"type":"message","id":"1aad7a46","parentId":"c3812c87","timestamp":"2026-02-13T18:33:26.613Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Repository Absence**\n\nI've hit a roadblock: the expected GitHub repository is returning a 404 error. My current hypothesis is that the user either has the project files locally or that the repository exists under a slightly different name. I'm moving forward by searching for \"DMarket Telegram Bot\" to see if I can locate the correct repository.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771007605951_187","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/engine.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12571,"output":226,"cacheRead":8185,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12797,"cost":{"input":0.025141999999999998,"output":0.002712,"cacheRead":0.0016370000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029490999999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771007600057}}
{"type":"message","id":"4535d7d1","parentId":"1aad7a46","timestamp":"2026-02-13T18:33:26.632Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771007605951_187","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import asyncio\nimport logging\nimport traceback\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport aiofiles\n\n# Conceptual integration for LOG agent\nLOG_AGENT_FILE = \"ERROR_LOG.md\"\n\nclass HybridEngine:\n    def __init__(self, dmarket_api, waxpeer_api):\n        self.dm = dmarket_api\n        self.wp = waxpeer_api\n        self.running = False\n\n    async def run(self):\n        self.running = True\n        logging.info(\"Engine started.\")\n        while self.running:\n            try:\n                # Main trading loop logic here (placeholder)\n                await asyncio.sleep(1)\n            except Exception as e:\n                # Use async error handling\n                await self.handle_error(e)\n                # Pause execution instead of immediate retry\n                await asyncio.sleep(10) \n\n    async def handle_error(self, e):\n        \"\"\"Async error logging to prevent blocking the event loop.\"\"\"\n        error_msg = traceback.format_exc()\n        \n        # Async Log for Console/File via aiofiles (Replacing blocking logging calls)\n        try:\n            async with aiofiles.open(\"engine.log\", \"a\") as f:\n                 await f.write(f\"[{datetime.now()}] CRITICAL ERROR: {e}\\n\")\n\n            async with aiofiles.open(LOG_AGENT_FILE, \"a\") as f:\n                await f.write(f\"\\n## ERROR REPORT - {datetime.now()}\\n\")\n                await f.write(f\"Type: {type(e).__name__}\\n\")\n                await f.write(f\"Details: {str(e)}\\n\")\n                await f.write(f\"Traceback:\\n```\\n{error_msg}\\n```\\n\")\n                await f.write(\"**ACTION REQUIRED:** LOG Agent (System Diagnostician) - Analyze and prescribe fix.\\n\")\n        except Exception as log_err:\n             # Fallback to print if async logging fails entirely\n             print(f\"Failed to write error log asynchronously: {log_err}\")\n        \n        # Notify about pause\n        try:\n            async with aiofiles.open(\"engine.log\", \"a\") as f:\n                await f.write(f\"[{datetime.now()}] Error logged for LOG agent analysis. Pausing main loop.\\n\")\n        except:\n            pass\n\n    def stop(self):\n        self.running = False\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771007606630}}
